  You’ll usually need a visa to come to the UK
<% end %>

<% govspeak_for :body do %>
  In most cases, you must apply for a [Standard Visitor visa](/standard-visitor-visa).

  ##When you might not need a visa

  You may be able to apply to come to the UK for free instead of paying for a visa if your partner or family member is a British citizen or from another European country.

  ###If your family member is a British citizen

  If you’ve been living with your British partner or family member in another European country, you may be able to make a 'Surinder Singh' application for a free [family permit](/family-permit/surinder-singh). Eligible countries are [countries in the EU](/eu-eea), Switzerland, Norway, Iceland and Liechtenstein.

  ###If your family member is from another European country

  You may be able to apply for a free [family permit](https://www.gov.uk/family-permit) if your partner or family member is from the EU, Switzerland, Norway, Iceland or Liechtenstein. They must have been living in the UK before 1 January 2021.
<% end %>
